    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Useful Information</para>
    <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Common materials for cam discs, cylindrical cams (drum cams) are, for example: </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Structural steels: S235, S355, etc. </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Case-hardening steels: 16MnCr5, 20MnCr5, 18CrNiMo7-6 etc. </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Tempered steels: C45, C60, 42CrMo4, 36CrNiMo4, etc. </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Tool steels: X100CrMov5, X155CrMoV12, etc. </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Corrosion Resistance Steels: 1.4112, 1.4301, 1.4404, 1.4462 etc. </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Casting materials: GJS 500, GJS 600, etc. </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Special steels: Inconel, Böhler K340, etc. </li>
      <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Plastics: PA 6, POM, Lauramid, etc.</li>
    </list>
